If a macro has a backslash(\) contained within the definition, the macro is ignored.  Probably wouldn't have noticed this except the the WYSIWYG editor seems to like to insert backslashes in various places, especially in front of | which are used in macros.

Examples:

{note:title=\test} {note}
{children:depth=3\|sort=none}
{noformat}

