We are starting to use our copy of Confluence *a lot* at StatPro.  I'm not sure if you are aware of it, but your mail capabilities are the thing that differentiate your product from most other Wiki's...why?  Because in most organisations people can't be bothered to log in and add pages.  However it is easy for people to simply cc emails to the Wiki.  As a result, the mail section of the Wiki is now *FULL* of amazing information.  It would be amazing if an user with editing rights could look at a particular mail and then convert it into a normal wiki page.  This way the wiki can be beautifully maintained and mails can then start to form part of the main body content of a space.  This would be a truly great feature.

